thread.title: Cardinals claim second in triangular

author: Herald Staff Report
title: Cardinals claim second in triangular
text:
Cardinals claim second in triangular Herald Staff Report The Clinton Herald 
ERIE, Ill. -- Erie had its final tuneup before Wednesdayâ€™ girls golf regional tournament and finished second in a triangular meet Monday at Lake Erie Country Club. 
Led by co-medalists Kassie Doyle and Taylor Newswander, Mercer County won the team title with a 194-stroke total. All four Mercer County scorers shot either a 48 or 49 on the par-37 course. 
Erie, playing without top scorer Sera Bebon, finished at 215. Madison Newton, Riley Redell and Sharon Kuhlemier each shot 53 to lead the Cardinals. 
ERIE TRIANGULAR 
Lake Erie Country Club, par 37 
Team standings 
1. Mercer County 194; 2. Erie 215; 3. Mid-County 218. 
Co-medalists -- Kassie Doyle (MC), Taylor Newswander (MC) 48. 
ERIE -- Madison Newton 53, Riley Redell 52, Sharon Kuhlemier 53, Heather Coers 56, Lexus Georgean 57. 
MERCER COUNTY -- Doyle 48, Newswander 48, Kayla Clawson 49, Bree Elliott 49, Madi Magendanz 52, Hannah Harrison 56.
